## What Assaults are most common among each Bias/Borough Group?
### Bias

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYmlhcyA8LSBIYXRlQ3JpbWVzJGBCaWFzIE1vdGl2ZSBEZXNjcmlwdGlvbmBcbmJpYXMgPC0gYXMuZGF0YS5mcmFtZSh0YWJsZShiaWFzKSlcbmJpYXMxIDwtIGJpYXNbb3JkZXIoYmlhcyRGcmVxKSxdXG52aWV3KGJpYXMxKVxuYGBgIn0= -->

```r
bias <- HateCrimes$`Bias Motive Description`
bias <- as.data.frame(table(bias))
bias1 <- bias[order(bias$Freq),]
view(bias1)
```

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

<!-- rnb-chunk-end -->


<!-- rnb-text-begin -->



<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin  -->

```r
## Make the frequencies numbers (rather than factors)
bias1$Freq <- as.numeric(as.character(bias1$Freq))
## Find a range of y's that'll leave sufficient space above the tallest bar
ylim <- c(0, 1.1*max(bias1$Freq))
## Plot, and store x-coordinates of bars in xx
xx <- barplot(bias1$Freq, xaxt = 'n', xlab = '', width = 0.85, ylim = ylim,
              main = "Bar Chart of Bias Motives", 
              ylab = "Frequency",
              col = "cadetblue2")
## Add text at top of bars
text(x = xx, y = bias1$Freq, label = bias1$Freq, pos = 3, cex = 0.8, col = "black")
## Add x-axis labels 
axis(1, at=xx, labels=bias1$bias, tick=FALSE, las=2, line=-0.5, cex.axis=0.5)

```

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

<!-- rnb-chunk-end -->


<!-- rnb-text-begin -->



<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin  -->

<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYm9yb3VnaCA8LSBIYXRlQ3JpbWVzJGBQYXRyb2wgQm9yb3VnaCBOYW1lYFxuYm9yb3VnaCA8LSBhcy5kYXRhLmZyYW1lKHRhYmxlKGJvcm91Z2gpKVxuYm9yb3VnaDEgPC0gYm9yb3VnaFtvcmRlcihib3JvdWdoJEZyZXEpLF1cbnZpZXcoYm9yb3VnaDEpXG5gYGAifQ== -->

```r
borough <- HateCrimes$`Patrol Borough Name`
borough <- as.data.frame(table(borough))
borough1 <- borough[order(borough$Freq),]
view(borough1)
```

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

<!-- rnb-chunk-end -->


<!-- rnb-text-begin -->




<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin  -->

```r
## Make the frequencies numbers (rather than factors)
borough1$Freq <- as.numeric(as.character(borough1$Freq))
## Find a range of y's that'll leave sufficient space above the tallest bar
ylim1 <- c(0, 1.1*max(borough1$Freq))
## Plot, and store x-coordinates of bars in xx
xx1 <- barplot(borough1$Freq, xaxt = 'n', xlab = '', width = 0.85, ylim = ylim1,
              main = "Bar Chart of Hate Crimes in Each Borough", 
              ylab = "Frequency",
              col = "cadetblue2")
## Add text at top of bars
text(x = xx1, y = borough1$Freq, label = borough1$Freq, pos = 3, cex = 0.8, col = "black")
```

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuIyMgQWRkIHgtYXhpcyBsYWJlbHMgXG5heGlzKDEsIGF0PXh4MSwgbGFiZWxzPWJvcm91Z2gxJGJvcm91Z2gsIHRpY2s9RkFMU0UsIGxhcz0yLCBsaW5lPS0wLjUsIGNleC5heGlzPTAuNSlcblxuYGBgIn0= -->

```r
## Add x-axis labels 
axis(1, at=xx1, labels=borough1$borough, tick=FALSE, las=2, line=-0.5, cex.axis=0.5)

```
